-- UniCredit, Intesa Among 13 Italian Banks Cut by Moody’s
-- B y   S t e v e n   N o r t o n
-- 2012-08-03T19:51:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-03/unicredit-intesa-among-13-italian-banks-cut-by-moody-s.html
UniCredit SpA (UCG)  and  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP) 
had their credit grades affirmed by  Standard & Poor’s  as the
ratings company downgraded 15 smaller lenders.  UniCredit,  Italy ’s biggest bank, and Intesa, the nation’s
second-largest, were among 15 companies whose ratings weren’t
changed in a review of 32 firms, S&P said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
